  "research_html": "<div class=\"research-section\">\n<p class=\"research-text\">The Epigram is a short verse composition attributed to Plato the Comic Poet, an Athenian poet of Old Comedy who was a contemporary of Aristophanes and active in the late fifth and early fourth centuries BCE. While Plato is known primarily for his comedies, the attribution of an epigram is consistent with the practice of poets composing in multiple forms. The work is fragmentary, and its specific content and structure are not detailed in surviving sources. As the text is not preserved, its precise subjects are unknown, though ancient Greek epigrams generally treated themes of commemoration, mortality, wit, satire, and praise. The epigram would survive, if at all, among the approximately 300 extant fragments of Plato’s work, preserved through quotation by later authors such as Athenaeus or potentially within anthologies like the Palatine Anthology. Any surviving epigram would extend our understanding of Plato the Comic Poet’s literary range beyond the comic stage. He was a significant figure in Old Comedy, and his works continued to be read and performed for centuries.</p>\n</div>",
  "rows": [
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 359.1.1",
      "text": "Ποίην τις βιότοιο τάμοι τρίβον; εἰν ἀγορῇ μὲν",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 359.1.2",
      "text": "νείκεα καὶ χαλεπαὶ πρήξιες, ἐν δὲ δόμοις",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 359.1.3",
      "text": "φροντίδες· ἐν δ’ ἀγροῖς καμάτων ἅλις, ἐν δὲ θαλάσσῃ",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 359",
      "text": "τάρβος· ἐπὶ ξείνης δ’, ἢν μὲν ἔχῃς τι, δέος·",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 359.5.1",
      "text": "ἢν δ’ ἀπορῇς, ἀνιηρόν. ἔχεις γάμον; οὐκ ἀμέριμνος",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 359.5.2",
      "text": "ἔσσεαι. οὐ γαμέεις; ζῇς ἔτ’ ἐρημότερος.",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 359.5.3",
      "text": "τέκνα πόνοι, πήρωσις ἄπαις βίος. αἱ νεότητες",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 359.5.4",
      "text": "ἄφρονες, αἱ πολιαὶ δ’ ἔμπαλιν ἀδρανέες.",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 359.5.5",
      "text": "ἦν ἄρα τοῖν δοιοῖν ἑνὸς αἵρεσις, ἢ τὸ γενέσθαι",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "book 359.10",
      "text": "μηδέποτ’ ἢ τὸ θανεῖν αὐτίκα τικτόμενον.",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    }
  ],
